    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dressing tables with two drawers in the sides which swing out and provide mirrors on a quadrant so that a woman could see herself at any angle.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000011251/Edwards and Macquoid, Dictionary of English Furniture, 2d ed. (1983)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mesas de tocador con dos cajones oscilantes en los costados que proveen de espejos en un cuadrante para que una mujer se puede ver de cualquier ángulo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
